res.json({ status: 'ok', timestamp: new Date().toISOString() });

// ✅ RECOMMENDED — minimal disclosure
res.json({ status: 'ok' });
```

---

#### 8. **No CORS Policy**

No CORS headers are configured. Depending on deployment context, this either blocks legitimate cross-origin use or (if using a permissive default elsewhere) allows hostile origins to make credentialed requests.

```js
// ✅ RECOMMENDED — explicit allowlist
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourdomain.com'],
  methods: ['GET'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Authorization', 'Content-Type'],
}));
```

---

#### 9. **No Request Body Size Limit**

While there are no `POST` endpoints today, the app has no body parser or payload size limits. Adding any body-accepting route in the future will be immediately vulnerable to large-payload DoS attacks.

