|---|----------|----------|-------|
| 1 | 🔴 Critical | OWASP A01 | No authentication on `/users` |
| 2 | 🔴 Critical | OWASP A05 | No security headers (no `helmet`) |
| 3 | 🔴 Critical | OWASP A05 | No rate limiting (DoS risk) |
| 4 | 🟠 High | OWASP A02 | No HTTPS enforcement |
| 5 | 🟠 High | OWASP A02 | PII hardcoded / future SQL injection risk |
| 6 | 🟠 High | OWASP A09 | No access logging or monitoring |
| 7 | 🟡 Medium | OWASP A05 | Timestamp disclosure in `/health` |
| 8 | 🟡 Medium | OWASP A05 | No CORS policy |
| 9 | 🟡 Medium | OWASP A05 | No request body size limits |
| 10 | 🟡 Medium | OWASP A05 | No global error handler (stack trace leakage) |

The most urgent fixes are **#1 (auth)**, **#2 (helmet)**, and **#3 (rate limiting)** — all can be added in minutes with existing npm packages.

